{{Flavour|The rarest of the salamander castes, possessed of fearsome agility and unparallelled martial prowess. Their mastery of fire is woven into every strike of their weapons, filling the air around their opponent with sweltering flames.}}

==Useful Info==
'''Salamander firebrands''' were fast-moving [[list of nagas#Salamander Types|salamanders]] which created a ring of flame [[cloud]]s around their enemies when they attacked in melee. They could be found in the [[Snake Pit]], [[the Depths]] and the [[Vestibule of Hell]].

==Tips & Tricks==
*As is the case with all salamanders, [[fire]] resistance greatly reduces the threat they pose. With sufficient resistance and [[AC]], you can likely ignore the flame clouds they produce without taking much damage. If you ''don't'' have fire resistance, however, consider [[blink]]ing if you need to escape without getting scorched.

==History==
*Salamander firebrands were removed in [[0.18]].
*Salamander firebrands were added in [[0.14]].
